definition: (of a car, ship, train etc) to enter
to gallop/speedily/to proceed to/to pilot (ship, plane etc)/to sail
to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]

sentences.english: The Australian government has indicated that a prosecution will follow because the ship ran aground in a no-go zone.
sentences.chinese: 澳大利亞政府提出起訴因爲船隻駛入了禁止區域。

sentences.english: The car has slowly, hard into the track.
sentences.chinese: 車子又緩緩的，艱難的駛入了正軌。

sentences.english: It turns out that the driver is a fugitive, who hijacks the family's car.
sentences.chinese: 兇徒劫持了這家人，驅車駛入深山之中。

sentences.english: He has a stern face and he simply nods before shooting off into the gathering darkness.
sentences.chinese: 他一臉嚴肅地點點頭，開車駛入越來越濃的夜色中。

sentences.english: I drove into Rome on a tank when the city was liberated.
sentences.chinese: 當時我開着一輛坦克駛入剛剛被解放的羅馬城。

sentences.english: Mukherjee has now seen many patients voyage into the night.
sentences.chinese: 現在，穆克吉看見許多癌症病人的航程駛入了黑夜。

sentences.english: The beach defences were softened up before the landing craft was in.
sentences.chinese: 在登陸艇駛入以前，海灘防禦工事已遭削弱。

sentences.english: There can be no pause until you come into port.
sentences.chinese: 在你駛入碼頭之前，你不可能停留。

sentences.english: The robber ditched the cops by driving down an alley.
sentences.chinese: 那竊賊把車駛入小巷躲開了警察。

sentences.english: Kashmiri fisherman rows his boat through autumn leaves in Kashmir's Dal Lake in Srinagar.
sentences.chinese: 一位克什米爾漁民撐船駛入秋天的斯里那加戴爾湖。

sentences.english: The purpose of the visit was to navigate into an ice-filled fiord.
sentences.chinese: 這次出行是爲了能駛入冰雪覆蓋的峽灣。

sentences.english: Finally, we destinated to climb the mountain.
sentences.chinese: 最後，我們駛入攀登高山。

sentences.english: Drive past this sign or drive on the road to which the ban applies.
sentences.chinese: 學習駕駛者不可駛越此標誌，或駛入禁止學車的道路。

sentences.english: He steamed the ship slowly into port.
sentences.chinese: 他把船緩慢地駛入港口。

sentences.english: Please drive along the cement road, do not into the grassland…
sentences.chinese: 球車請沿水泥路行駛，請勿駛入草地。

sentences.english: A mrt train was entering the station Fu-Hsing Kang.
sentences.chinese: 駛入復興崗站的捷運列車。
